<TEXT>
<HTML><HEAD>
<TITLE>EX-99.1</TITLE>
</HEAD>
 <BODY BGCOLOR="WHITE">

 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman" ALIGN="right"><B>Exhibit 99.1 </B></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman" ALIGN="center"><B>Recro Pharma Announces Additional Information for Phase II Clinical Trial of Dex-IN </B></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman" ALIGN="center"><I>Additional safety and efficacy information provided </I></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">MALVERN, PA, July&nbsp;24, 2015 &#150; Recro Pharma, Inc. (Nasdaq: REPH), a revenue generating specialty pharmaceutical company developing multiple non-opioid
therapeutics for the treatment of acute post operative pain, today announced additional results from the Phase II clinical trial for Dex-IN, a proprietary intranasal formulation of dexmedetomidine, for the treatment of acute pain in adult patients
undergoing bunionectomy surgery. As previously released, Dex-IN met the primary endpoint of the clinical trial in demonstrating significant pain relief compared with placebo over 48 hours (p=0.0214). The Company plans to meet with the FDA to discuss
the Company&#146;s Phase III plans and determine what, if any, additional information will be required in association with the Phase III clinical program for Dex-IN. </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">The Phase II trial was a randomized, multicenter, double-blind, placebo-controlled study to evaluate the efficacy and safety of Recro Pharma&#146;s
proprietary intranasal formulation of dexmedetomidine, Dex-IN, in adult patients undergoing bunionectomy surgery, initiating dosing of study medication on Post Op Day 1. Patients who met the eligibility criteria were randomized to either a
50&micro;g dose of Dex-IN or a placebo intranasal dose given every 6 hours. Following the beginning of treatment, patients remained under observation for 48 hours at study centers. Patients were followed for 7 days after the initial dose of study
medication. There was an oral opioid rescue treatment available to patients in either treatment group, if required, to provide adequate pain relief. A total of 168 patients were randomized and received study medication in the clinical trial, 84
patients in each treatment group. The key subject characteristics are listed in Table 1 below. The one discontinued subject was for a serious adverse event of hypotension. </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:18pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman"><B>Table 1: Summary of Key Subject Characteristics REC-14-013 </B></P> <P STYLE="font-size:12pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE CELLSPACING="0" CELLPADDING="0" WIDTH="76%" BORDER="0" STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt" ALIGN="center">


<TR>
<TD WIDTH="76%"></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" WIDTH="4%"></TD>
<TD></TD>
<TD></TD>
<TD></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" WIDTH="4%"></TD>
<TD></TD>
<TD></TD>
<TD></TD></TR>
<TR STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:8pt">
<TD VALIGN="bottom">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom">&nbsp;&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" COLSPAN="2" ALIGN="center"><B>Placebo</B></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom">&nbsp;&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" COLSPAN="2" ALIGN="center"><B><FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">DEX-IN&nbsp;50&nbsp;&micro;g</FONT></B></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom">&nbsp;</TD></TR>
<TR STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:8pt">
<TD VALIGN="bottom" NOWRAP> <P STYLE="border-bottom:1.00pt solid #000000; width:48.80pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:Times New Roman"><B>Characteristic</B></P></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom">&nbsp;&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" COLSPAN="2" ALIGN="center" STYLE="border-bottom:1.00pt solid #000000"><B>(N = 84)</B></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom">&nbsp;&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" COLSPAN="2" ALIGN="center" STYLE="border-bottom:1.00pt solid #000000"><B>(N =84)</B></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom">&nbsp;</TD></TR>


<TR BGCOLOR="#cceeff" STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:10pt">
<TD VALIGN="top"> <P STYLE="margin-left:1.00em; text-indent:-1.00em; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">Female, n (%)</P></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom">&nbsp;&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" ALIGN="right">75&nbsp;(89.3</TD>
<TD NOWRAP VALIGN="bottom">)&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom">&nbsp;&nbsp;</TD>

</TABLE> <P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">The primary efficacy endpoint of the trial was the summed pain intensity difference over 48 hours, SPID48, utilizing the last
observation carry forward analysis method. Additional efficacy endpoints included use of opioid rescue medication, SPIDs over various time intervals, as well as other standard efficacy analyses. An adverse event of bradycardia was reported in 3
subjects in the Dex-IN treatment group. No patients with blood pressure decrease, hypotension nor with bradycardia required medication to treat these events. The most frequently reported adverse events reported in the Dex-IN group from the
REC-14-013 trial are summarized in Table 2 below. </P>

<P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">Bunionectomy surgery generally involves an incision in the top or side of the big toe joint and the removal or realignment of soft tissue and bone. This is
done to relieve pain and restore normal alignment to the joint. Bunionectomy surgery typically results in intense post operative pain. In the past, drugs that have demonstrated analgesic effectiveness following bunionectomy surgery have frequently
translated that analgesic success into other post operative procedures that result in moderate to severe, acute pain. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:18pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman"><B>About Recro Pharma, Inc.
</B></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">Recro Pharma is a revenue generating specialty pharmaceutical company developing multiple non-opioid therapeutics for the treatment of acute post
operative pain. Recro Pharma is currently developing IV/IM meloxicam, a proprietary, Phase III-ready, long-acting preferential COX-2 inhibitor, and Dex-IN, a proprietary intranasal formulation of dexmedetomidine that has completed Phase II clinical
trials, for the treatment of acute post operative pain. As Recro Pharma&#146;s product candidates are not in the opioid class of drugs, the Company believes its candidates would avoid many of the side effects associated with commonly prescribed
opioid therapeutics, such as addiction, constipation and respiratory distress, while maintaining analgesic effect. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman">Recro Pharma also owns and operates an
87,000 square foot, DEA-licensed facility that manufactures five commercial products and receives royalties associated with the sales of these products. </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:18pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:Times New Roman"><B>Cautionary Statement Regarding Forward Looking Statements </B></P>

the Company&#146;s ability to raise future financing for continued development; the performance of third-party suppliers and manufacturers; the Company&#146;s ability to obtain, maintain and successfully enforce adequate patent and other

style='font-style:normal;font-weight:normal;font-size:24px;font-family:calibri,arial,sans-serif;color:#004964;'>$0.0</font></div> <div style='position:absolute;left:848px;top:345px;'><font
style='font-style:normal;font-weight:normal;font-size:24px;font-family:calibri,arial,sans-serif;color:#004964;'>$0.0</font></div> <div style='position:absolute;left:77px;top:384px;'><font
style='font-style:normal;font-weight:normal;font-size:24px;font-family:calibri,arial,sans-serif;color:#004964;'>Depreciation and amortization</font></div> <div style='position:absolute;left:500px;top:384px;'><font
style='font-style:normal;font-weight:normal;font-size:24px;font-family:calibri,arial,sans-serif;color:#004964;'>$10.3</font></div> <div style='position:absolute;left:680px;top:384px;'><font
style='font-style:normal;font-weight:normal;font-size:24px;font-family:calibri,arial,sans-serif;color:#004964;'>$2.9</font></div> <div style='position:absolute;left:848px;top:384px;'><font
style='font-style:normal;font-weight:normal;font-size:24px;font-family:calibri,arial,sans-serif;color:#004964;'>$2.5</font></div> <div style='position:absolute;left:77px;top:423px;'><font
style='font-style:normal;font-weight:normal;font-size:24px;font-family:calibri,arial,sans-serif;color:#004964;'>EBITDA</font></div> <div style='position:absolute;left:500px;top:423px;'><font
style='font-style:normal;font-weight:normal;font-size:24px;font-family:calibri,arial,sans-serif;color:#004964;'>$29.2</font></div> <div style='position:absolute;left:680px;top:423px;'><font
style='font-style:normal;font-weight:normal;font-size:24px;font-family:calibri,arial,sans-serif;color:#004964;'>$5.2</font></div> <div style='position:absolute;left:848px;top:423px;'><font
style='font-style:normal;font-weight:normal;font-size:24px;font-family:calibri,arial,sans-serif;color:#004964;'>$6.8</font></div> <div style='position:absolute;left:876px;top:694px;'><font
style='font-style:normal;font-weight:normal;font-size:13px;font-family:arial,sans-serif;color:#FFFFFF;'>38</font></div> <div style='position:absolute;left:69px;top:496px;'><font
style='font-style:normal;font-weight:normal;font-size:19px;font-family:arial,sans-serif;color:#004964;'>The Company defines EBITDA as earnings before interest, taxes, depreciation and amortization. The </font></div>
<div style='position:absolute;left:69px;top:519px;'><font style='font-style:normal;font-weight:normal;font-size:19px;font-family:arial,sans-serif;color:#004964;'>Company also presents EBITDA because it believes it is frequently used by securities
analysts, </font></div> <div style='position:absolute;left:69px;top:541px;'><font style='font-style:normal;font-weight:normal;font-size:19px;font-family:arial,sans-serif;color:#004964;'>investors and other interested parties as a measure of
financial performance. EBITDA has limitations as </font></div> <div style='position:absolute;left:69px;top:563px;'><font style='font-style:normal;font-weight:normal;font-size:19px;font-family:arial,sans-serif;color:#004964;'>an analytical tool, and
when assessing the Company's operating performance, investors should not </font></div>
<div style='position:absolute;left:69px;top:586px;'><font style='font-style:normal;font-weight:normal;font-size:19px;font-family:arial,sans-serif;color:#004964;'>consider EBITDA in isolation, or as a substitute for net income (loss) or other
consolidated income </font></div> <div style='position:absolute;left:69px;top:608px;'><font style='font-style:normal;font-weight:normal;font-size:19px;font-family:arial,sans-serif;color:#004964;'>statement data prepared in accordance with U.S. GAAP.
</font></div> </td></tr></table></div> </BODY></HTML>
